Quote:  We had three glorious days pig-shooting in the "Tobacco Country," a wild waste of bog and bush land lying across the south of the island [sc. in the Chathams] so called because it was bought by a speculative white in the early days from the Maori conquerors for a box or barrel of tobacco.
